																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">15</div> <div class="vers-content">welcome the sight when it shews itself, when it gives proof of its wondrous power.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">16</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom, and was created with the faithful in the womb, it walketh with chosen women, and is known with the just and faithful.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">16</div> <div class="vers-content">Initium sapientiÃ¦ timor Domini: et cum fidelibus in vulva concreatus est: cum electis feminis graditur, et cum justis et fidelibus agnoscitur.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">16</div> <div class="vers-content">Wouldst thou be wise, the first step is fear of the Lord; to his chosen servants, a gift connatural from the womb; it goes with holy motherhood, and where his true worshippers are, shews manifest.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">17</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord is the religiousness of knowledge.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">17</div> <div class="vers-content">Timor Domini scientiÃ¦ religiositas:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">17</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord lends wisdom that piety which is hers;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">Religiousness shall keep and justify the heart, it shall give joy and gladness.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">religiositas custodiet et justificabit cor; jucunditatem atque gaudium dabit.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">such piety as shall keep the heart safe and make it acceptable, bring it joy and content.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">It shall go well with him that feareth the Lord, and in the days of his end he shall be blessed.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">Timenti Dominum bene erit, et in diebus consummationis illius benedicetur.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">Well it shall be indeed for the man who fears the Lord; at his last end he shall win blessing.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">To fear God is the fulness of wisdom, and fulness is from the fruits thereof.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">Plenitudo sapientiÃ¦ est timere Deum, et plenitudo a fructibus illius.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord is wisdomâ€™s fulfilment, yields the deep draught that satisfies;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">She shall fill all her house with her increase, and the storehouses with her treasures.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">Omnem domum illius implebit a generationibus, et receptacula a thesauris illius.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">never a nook or cranny in thy house but shall be filled with the store of its harvesting.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord is a crown of wisdom, filling up peace and the fruit of salvation:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">Corona sapientiÃ¦ timor Domini, replens pacem et salutis fructum:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord is wisdomâ€™s crown; with this, peace and health are thine to enjoy;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">And it hath seen, and numbered her: but both are the gifts of God.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">et vidit, et dinumeravit eam: utraque autem sunt dona Dei.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">this fear itself is Godâ€™s gift, no less than the wisdom which is counted out under his eye.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Wisdom shall distribute knowledge, and understanding of prudence: and exalteth the glory of them that hold her.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Scientiam et intellectum prudentiÃ¦ sapientia compartietur, et gloriam tenentium se exaltat.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Wisdom it is that imparts to us all our knowledge, all our powers of discernment; hold her fast, and she will set thee on a pinnacle of renown;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">The root of wisdom is to fear the Lord: and the branches thereof are long-lived.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">Radix sapientiÃ¦ est timere Dominum, et rami illius longÃ¦vi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">root of her is fear of the Lord, and long life the fruit of her.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">In the treasures of wisdom is understanding, and religiousness of knowledge: but to sinners wisdom is an abomination.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">In thesauris sapientiÃ¦ intellectus et scientiÃ¦ religiositas: execratio autem peccatoribus sapientia.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">True insight wisdom has in her treasure-house, and the piety that comes of knowledge; no wonder if sinners hate the name of her.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord driveth out sin:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Timor Domini expellit peccatum:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">The fear of the Lord drives out sin;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">For he that is without fear, cannot be justified: for the wrath of his high spirits is his ruin.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">nam qui sine timore est non poterit justificari: iracundia enim animositatis illius subversio illius est.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">soul that feels no fear shall find no pardon, its own wild mood overbalances it.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">A patient man shall bear for a time, and afterwards joy shall be restored to him.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Usque in tempus sustinebit patiens, et postea redditio jucunditatis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Patience bides her time, and with time, content comes back to her;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">A good understanding will hide his words for a time, and the lips of many shall declare his wisdom.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">Bonus sensus usque in tempus abscondet verba illius, et labia multorum enarrabunt sensum illius.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">praise shall be upon every lip for the wise thought that checked, for a while, her utterance.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">In the treasures of wisdom is the signification of discipline:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">In thesauris sapientiÃ¦ significatio disciplinÃ¦:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">Hidden in wisdomâ€™s treasure-house is the secret of all discernment;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">But the worship of God is an abomination to a sinner.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">execratio autem peccatori cultura Dei.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">and still sinners hate the name of piety.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Son, if thou desire wisdom, keep justice, and God will give her to thee.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Fili, concupiscens sapientiam, conserva justitiam, et Deus prÃ¦bebit illam tibi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">My son, if on wisdom thy heart is set, keep the commandments, and God will grant thy wish;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">For the fear of the Lord is wisdom and discipline: and that which is agreeable to him,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">Sapientia enim et disciplina timor Domini: et quod beneplacitum est illi,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">fear of the Lord is true wisdom, true learning, and his will</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">Is faith, and meekness: and he will fill up his treasures.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">fides et mansuetudo, et adimplebit thesauros illius.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">is to see thee loyal and patient; thou shalt have no empty coffers then.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">Be not incredulous to the fear of the Lord: and come not to him with a double heart.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">Ne sis incredibilis timori Domini, et ne accesseris ad illum duplici corde.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">Let not thy fear of the Lord be overcast with doubt; never come to him with a heart that hesitates.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">37</div> <div class="vers-content">Be not a hypocrite in the sight of men, and let not thy lips be a stumblingblock to thee.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">37</div> <div class="vers-content">Ne fueris hypocrita in conspectu hominum, et non scandalizeris in labiis tuis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">37</div> <div class="vers-content">Do not play false in thy dealings with men, nor suffer thy own words to ensnare thee.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">38</div> <div class="vers-content">Watch over them, lest thou fall, and bring dishonour upon thy soul,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">38</div> <div class="vers-content">Attende in illis, ne forte cadas, et adducas animÃ¦ tuÃ¦ inhonorationem:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">38</div> <div class="vers-content">Watch those words well, or they may trip thee up; thou wilt have compassed thy own disgrace,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">39</div> <div class="vers-content">And God discover thy secrets, and cast thee down in the midst of the congregation.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">39</div> <div class="vers-content">et revelet Deus absconsa tua, et in medio synagogÃ¦ elidat te:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">39</div> <div class="vers-content">if God should reveal thy secret thoughts at last; wouldst thou be thrown down, in full sight of all thy neighbours assembled,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">40</div> <div class="vers-content">Because thou camest to the Lord wickedly, and thy heart is full of guile and deceit.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">40</div> <div class="vers-content">quoniam accessisti maligne ad Dominum, et cor tuum plenum est dolo et fallacia.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">40</div> <div class="vers-content">a heart that came to meet the Lord grudgingly, full all the while of treachery and deceit?</div></div></td>
